MongoDB Atlas
    Easy way to host and manage your data in the cloud. 
    Creating a cluster, connecting to it, inserting data, and querying data.

Use user guide 
    https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/getting-started/

Deployed a Free Tier Cluster after creation of Atlas account. 
    Sample_cluster_name:credentials = rt_usr_cluser_1:rt_usr_cluser_1

Java Connection: 

    MongoClientURI uri = new MongoClientURI(
        "mongodb+srv://rt_usr_cluser_1:<password>@rt-cluster-1-da72r.mongodb.net/test?retryWrites=true&w=majority");

    MongoClient mongoClient = new MongoClient(uri);
    MongoDatabase database = mongoClient.getDatabase("test");

Hands on github link: 
    https://github.com/aartijangid/TestUrSkills/tree/master/src/test/java/connect/mongodb
